  "prompt": "How do I transfer WhatsApp messages from to iOS Android?",
  "response": "To transfer WhatsApp messages from Android to iOS, you'll need to use the following methods:\n\n1. Official Method (Recommended):\n- Use WhatsApp's built-in chat transfer feature\n- Requires both phones to be present\n- Steps:\n  a) Install WhatsApp on new iPhone\n  b) During setup, choose \"Transfer from Android\"\n  c) Ensure both phones are connected to same Wi-Fi\n  d) Follow on-screen instructions\n\n2. Third-Party Apps:\n- Use apps like:\n  - Dr. Fone - WhatsApp Transfer\n  - MobileTrans\n  - iSkysoft Phone Transfer\n- These typically require:\n  a) Download software on computer\n  b) Connect both phones via USB\n  c) Follow app's transfer instructions\n\n3. Google Drive Backup (Partial Method):\n- Back up WhatsApp on Android to Google Drive\n- Restore backup on new iPhone (limited functionality)\n\nImportant Notes:\n- Some methods might not transfer all media\n- Always backup your messages first\n- Some transfers may require payment\n- Exact steps can vary based on phone models\n\nRecommended: Use WhatsApp's official transfer method or a reputable third-party app for best results.",
